{"block_id": "B003", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 3, "start_line": 1115, "end_line": 1117, "raw_text": "In February 2013, Stephen I. Sadove, Saks\u0092 Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, received an unsolicited phone call from a representative of a private equity firm, which we refer to as Sponsor A,\nexpressing interest in a potential acquisition of Saks. In early March 2013, Mr. Sadove met with senior representatives of Sponsor A to discuss the possibility of a potential transaction. No specific proposals were made by Sponsor A, and no\nspecific transaction terms were discussed.", "clean_text": "In February 2013, Stephen I. Sadove, Saks\u0092 Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, received an unsolicited phone call from a representative of a private equity firm, which we refer to as Sponsor A, expressing interest in a potential acquisition of Saks. In early March 2013, Mr. Sadove met with senior representatives of Sponsor A to discuss the possibility of a potential transaction. No specific proposals were made by Sponsor A, and no specific transaction terms were discussed.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "February 2013", "normalized": "2013-02-01", "precision": "month"}, {"raw_text": "early March 2013", "normalized": "2013-03-05", "precision": "month_early"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B004", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 4, "start_line": 1119, "end_line": 1123, "raw_text": "On March 7, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled telephonic meeting. At this\nmeeting, Mr. Sadove informed the board of the contacts with Sponsor A. The board had a general discussion of potential strategic transactions, including a potential acquisition of Saks and the potential for Saks to make a strategic acquisition\nof a privately held retail company, which we refer to as Company B. The board requested that Saks\u0092 advisors and senior management provide the Finance committee of the board with ongoing updates with respect to these matters, and that the\nFinance committee provide guidance to Saks\u0092 advisors and senior management throughout the process of evaluating actions of this type, due to the expertise and background of the members of the Finance committee and the board\u0092s belief that\nit would be more efficient for a smaller group of directors than the entire board to receive more frequent updates.", "clean_text": "On March 7, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled telephonic meeting. At this meeting, Mr. Sadove informed the board of the contacts with Sponsor A. The board had a general discussion of potential strategic transactions, including a potential acquisition of Saks and the potential for Saks to make a strategic acquisition of a privately held retail company, which we refer to as Company B. The board requested that Saks\u0092 advisors and senior management provide the Finance committee of the board with ongoing updates with respect to these matters, and that the Finance committee provide guidance to Saks\u0092 advisors and senior management throughout the process of evaluating actions of this type, due to the expertise and background of the members of the Finance committee and the board\u0092s belief that it would be more efficient for a smaller group of directors than the entire board to receive more frequent updates.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 7, 2013", "normalized": "2013-03-07", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B005", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 5, "start_line": 1125, "end_line": 1127, "raw_text": "On April 1, 2013,\nMr. Sadove met with Richard Baker, the Director, Governor, and Chief Executive Officer of Hudson\u0092s Bay, at the request of Mr. Baker and discussed a potential acquisition of Saks by Hudson\u0092s Bay. No specific proposals were made by\nHudson\u0092s Bay, and no specific transaction terms were discussed.", "clean_text": "On April 1, 2013, Mr. Sadove met with Richard Baker, the Director, Governor, and Chief Executive Officer of Hudson\u0092s Bay, at the request of Mr. Baker and discussed a potential acquisition of Saks by Hudson\u0092s Bay. No specific proposals were made by Hudson\u0092s Bay, and no specific transaction terms were discussed.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 1, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-01", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B006", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 6, "start_line": 1129, "end_line": 1131, "raw_text": "On April 4, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled\ntelephonic meeting. At this meeting, Mr. Sadove reviewed with the board the expressions of interest in a potential acquisition of Saks from Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A. The board discussed these expressions of interest, as well as a\npotential strategic acquisition of Company B. The board directed Mr. Sadove and Saks management to continue exploring these potential transactions.", "clean_text": "On April 4, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled telephonic meeting. At this meeting, Mr. Sadove reviewed with the board the expressions of interest in a potential acquisition of Saks from Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A. The board discussed these expressions of interest, as well as a potential strategic acquisition of Company B. The board directed Mr. Sadove and Saks management to continue exploring these potential transactions.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 4, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-04", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B007", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 7, "start_line": 1133, "end_line": 1133, "raw_text": "-23-", "clean_text": "-23-", "is_heading": true, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "initiation"}
{"block_id": "B008", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 8, "start_line": 1136, "end_line": 1139, "raw_text": "On April 11, 2013, the Finance committee of the board and the Executive committee of the board held a\nspecial joint telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen & Katz, referred to as Wachtell Lipton, Saks\u0092 external counsel. At this meeting, Mr. Sadove updated the committee members on\ndiscussions with Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A regarding a potential acquisition of Saks, and discussed with the committee members the potential acquisition of Company B. The committee members directed that Mr. Sadove and Saks management\ncontinue evaluating these potential transactions.", "clean_text": "On April 11, 2013, the Finance committee of the board and the Executive committee of the board held a special joint telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen & Katz, referred to as Wachtell Lipton, Saks\u0092 external counsel. At this meeting, Mr. Sadove updated the committee members on discussions with Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A regarding a potential acquisition of Saks, and discussed with the committee members the potential acquisition of Company B. The committee members directed that Mr. Sadove and Saks management continue evaluating these potential transactions.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 11, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-11", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B009", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 9, "start_line": 1141, "end_line": 1143, "raw_text": "Following the April 11 joint committee meeting, representatives of Saks management and\nof Goldman Sachs met separately with representatives of two private equity firms, which we refer to as Sponsor C and Sponsor D, respectively, to discuss the possibility of their providing equity financing for an acquisition of Company B. Management\nand representatives of Saks and Sponsor C and Sponsor D continued these discussions over the next several weeks.", "clean_text": "Following the April 11 joint committee meeting, representatives of Saks management and of Goldman Sachs met separately with representatives of two private equity firms, which we refer to as Sponsor C and Sponsor D, respectively, to discuss the possibility of their providing equity financing for an acquisition of Company B. Management and representatives of Saks and Sponsor C and Sponsor D continued these discussions over the next several weeks.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April", "normalized": null, "precision": "unknown"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B010", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 10, "start_line": 1145, "end_line": 1145, "raw_text": "During the week of", "clean_text": "During the week of", "is_heading": true, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B011", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 11, "start_line": 1146, "end_line": 1148, "raw_text": "April 15, 2013, representatives of Goldman Sachs met separately with representatives of each of Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A in order to discuss their respective consideration of a potential acquisition of Saks. Each of Hudson\u0092s Bay and\nSponsor A indicated that they were considering making an offer to acquire Saks for at least $15 per share, in cash. A private equity firm that we refer to as Sponsor E and that Sponsor A had stated was in discussions with Sponsor A regarding\nparticipation in a potential joint acquisition of Saks also participated in the meeting with Sponsor A.", "clean_text": "April 15, 2013, representatives of Goldman Sachs met separately with representatives of each of Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A in order to discuss their respective consideration of a potential acquisition of Saks. Each of Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A indicated that they were considering making an offer to acquire Saks for at least $15 per share, in cash. A private equity firm that we refer to as Sponsor E and that Sponsor A had stated was in discussions with Sponsor A regarding participation in a potential joint acquisition of Saks also participated in the meeting with Sponsor A.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 15, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-15", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B012", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 12, "start_line": 1150, "end_line": 1151, "raw_text": "On April 17, 2013, Saks and\nSponsor C entered into a confidentiality agreement. On April 19, 2013, Saks and Sponsor D entered into a confidentiality agreement.", "clean_text": "On April 17, 2013, Saks and Sponsor C entered into a confidentiality agreement. On April 19, 2013, Saks and Sponsor D entered into a confidentiality agreement.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 17, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-17", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "April 19, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-19", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B013", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 13, "start_line": 1153, "end_line": 1156, "raw_text": "On April 25, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this\nmeeting, representatives of Goldman Sachs discussed with the board the following alternatives available to Saks \u0096 the potential acquisition of Saks by a third party, a potential acquisition of Company B and remaining as an independent public\ncompany. Mr. Sadove and Goldman Sachs updated the board on the status of discussions with Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A and Sponsor E, as well as the discussions with Sponsor C and Sponsor D regarding the possibility of providing equity\nfinancing for an acquisition of Company B if the board decided to pursue such a transaction.", "clean_text": "On April 25, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, representatives of Goldman Sachs discussed with the board the following alternatives available to Saks \u0096 the potential acquisition of Saks by a third party, a potential acquisition of Company B and remaining as an independent public company. Mr. Sadove and Goldman Sachs updated the board on the status of discussions with Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A and Sponsor E, as well as the discussions with Sponsor C and Sponsor D regarding the possibility of providing equity financing for an acquisition of Company B if the board decided to pursue such a transaction.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 25, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-25", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B014", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 14, "start_line": 1158, "end_line": 1159, "raw_text": "On April 26, 2013, Saks entered into a\nconfidentiality agreement with each of Sponsor A and Sponsor E, who were considering participating in a potential joint acquisition of Saks.", "clean_text": "On April 26, 2013, Saks entered into a confidentiality agreement with each of Sponsor A and Sponsor E, who were considering participating in a potential joint acquisition of Saks.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 26, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-26", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B015", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 15, "start_line": 1161, "end_line": 1161, "raw_text": "On April 30, 2013, Saks and Hudson\u0092s Bay entered into a confidentiality agreement.", "clean_text": "On April 30, 2013, Saks and Hudson\u0092s Bay entered into a confidentiality agreement.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 30, 2013", "normalized": "2013-04-30", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B016", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 16, "start_line": 1163, "end_line": 1164, "raw_text": "Following each party\u0092s entry into a confidentiality agreement, Saks made an online dataroom available to Sponsor A, Sponsor E and Hudson\u0092s Bay. Sponsor A, Sponsor E and Hudson\u0092s Bay each\nengaged in due diligence and meetings with Saks\u0092 management over the next several weeks.", "clean_text": "Following each party\u0092s entry into a confidentiality agreement, Saks made an online dataroom available to Sponsor A, Sponsor E and Hudson\u0092s Bay. Sponsor A, Sponsor E and Hudson\u0092s Bay each engaged in due diligence and meetings with Saks\u0092 management over the next several weeks.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B017", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 17, "start_line": 1166, "end_line": 1168, "raw_text": "During this period, members of Saks\u0092\nmanagement reviewed with the members of the Finance committee the terms of the equity financing for a potential acquisition of Company B that had been negotiated with Sponsor C and those that had been negotiated with Sponsor D. The committee members\ndetermined that the terms negotiated with Sponsor C were more favorable than those negotiated with Sponsor D.", "clean_text": "During this period, members of Saks\u0092 management reviewed with the members of the Finance committee the terms of the equity financing for a potential acquisition of Company B that had been negotiated with Sponsor C and those that had been negotiated with Sponsor D. The committee members determined that the terms negotiated with Sponsor C were more favorable than those negotiated with Sponsor D.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "other"}
{"block_id": "B018", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 18, "start_line": 1170, "end_line": 1174, "raw_text": "On May 15, 2013, the\nFinance committee of the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, Mr. Sadove and Goldman Sachs updated the committee on the status of discussions with\nHudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A and Sponsor E, including a request from Hudson\u0092s Bay that it be permitted under the confidentiality agreement it had signed with Saks to contact a limited number of potential sources of equity financing for a\npotential acquisition of Saks. The committee also discussed the potential acquisition of Company B. Following discussion, the Finance committee agreed to grant Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s request, subject to compliance with the terms of the\nconfidentiality agreement. The committee also recommended that management continue exploring the potential transactions described above.", "clean_text": "On May 15, 2013, the Finance committee of the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, Mr. Sadove and Goldman Sachs updated the committee on the status of discussions with Hudson\u0092s Bay and Sponsor A and Sponsor E, including a request from Hudson\u0092s Bay that it be permitted under the confidentiality agreement it had signed with Saks to contact a limited number of potential sources of equity financing for a potential acquisition of Saks. The committee also discussed the potential acquisition of Company B. Following discussion, the Finance committee agreed to grant Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s request, subject to compliance with the terms of the confidentiality agreement. The committee also recommended that management continue exploring the potential transactions described above.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 15, 2013", "normalized": "2013-05-15", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B019", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 19, "start_line": 1176, "end_line": 1176, "raw_text": "-24-", "clean_text": "-24-", "is_heading": true, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "other"}
{"block_id": "B020", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 20, "start_line": 1179, "end_line": 1181, "raw_text": "Following the May 15 committee meeting, Goldman Sachs contacted Company B\u0092s principal shareholders\nto express Saks\u0092 interest in exploring a potential acquisition of Company B. No proposals were made, and no specific transaction terms were discussed. During this period, representatives of Saks continued to discuss with representatives of\nSponsor C the possibility of Saks\u0092 making an offer to acquire Company B.", "clean_text": "Following the May 15 committee meeting, Goldman Sachs contacted Company B\u0092s principal shareholders to express Saks\u0092 interest in exploring a potential acquisition of Company B. No proposals were made, and no specific transaction terms were discussed. During this period, representatives of Saks continued to discuss with representatives of Sponsor C the possibility of Saks\u0092 making an offer to acquire Company B.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May", "normalized": null, "precision": "unknown"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B021", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 21, "start_line": 1183, "end_line": 1185, "raw_text": "On May 17, 2013, representatives of Goldman Sachs\norally communicated to the principal shareholders of Company B Saks\u0092 preliminary, non-binding proposal to acquire Company B in a cash transaction, with flexibility to include some stock consideration (which proposal Saks confirmed in a letter\non May 20, 2013). Shortly thereafter, the principal shareholders of Company B informed representatives of Goldman Sachs that the proposal was insufficient.", "clean_text": "On May 17, 2013, representatives of Goldman Sachs orally communicated to the principal shareholders of Company B Saks\u0092 preliminary, non-binding proposal to acquire Company B in a cash transaction, with flexibility to include some stock consideration (which proposal Saks confirmed in a letter on May 20, 2013). Shortly thereafter, the principal shareholders of Company B informed representatives of Goldman Sachs that the proposal was insufficient.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 17, 2013", "normalized": "2013-05-17", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "May 20, 2013", "normalized": "2013-05-20", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B022", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 22, "start_line": 1187, "end_line": 1187, "raw_text": "In late May 2013, media reports began to appear stating that Saks had engaged Goldman Sachs to explore a potential sale of Saks.", "clean_text": "In late May 2013, media reports began to appear stating that Saks had engaged Goldman Sachs to explore a potential sale of Saks.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "late May 2013", "normalized": "2013-05-25", "precision": "month_late"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B023", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 23, "start_line": 1189, "end_line": 1191, "raw_text": "On June 1, 2013, the Finance committee of the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, the committee reviewed with\nMr. Sadove and Saks\u0092 advisors the discussions with each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Company B\u0092s principal shareholders regarding potential transactions, including a financial evaluation of Company B. The committee determined\nto discuss the matters further with the full board at the next board meeting.", "clean_text": "On June 1, 2013, the Finance committee of the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, the committee reviewed with Mr. Sadove and Saks\u0092 advisors the discussions with each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Company B\u0092s principal shareholders regarding potential transactions, including a financial evaluation of Company B. The committee determined to discuss the matters further with the full board at the next board meeting.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June 1, 2013", "normalized": "2013-06-01", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B024", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 24, "start_line": 1193, "end_line": 1195, "raw_text": "During the week of June 3, 2013, representatives of\nGoldman Sachs spoke with representatives of each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Sponsor E and were informed that Hudson\u0092s Bay, on the one hand, and Sponsor A and Sponsor E, on the other hand, were each preliminarily prepared to proceed\nwith the submission of a proposal to acquire Saks at indicative price ranges of $15 to $15.25 per share of common stock (in the case of Hudson\u0092s Bay) and $15 to $16 per share of common stock (in the case of Sponsor A and Sponsor E).", "clean_text": "During the week of June 3, 2013, representatives of Goldman Sachs spoke with representatives of each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Sponsor E and were informed that Hudson\u0092s Bay, on the one hand, and Sponsor A and Sponsor E, on the other hand, were each preliminarily prepared to proceed with the submission of a proposal to acquire Saks at indicative price ranges of $15 to $15.25 per share of common stock (in the case of Hudson\u0092s Bay) and $15 to $16 per share of common stock (in the case of Sponsor A and Sponsor E).", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June 3, 2013", "normalized": "2013-06-03", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B025", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 25, "start_line": 1197, "end_line": 1200, "raw_text": "On June 5, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting,\nthe board reviewed with Mr. Sadove and Saks\u0092 advisors the discussions with each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Company B\u0092s principal shareholders regarding potential transactions, and authorized (1) the implementation of a\nprocess to determine whether a transaction with one of the potential acquirors which had executed a confidentiality agreement could be reached on terms that would offer attractive value to Saks shareholders and (2) the submission of a revised\nproposal to acquire Company B.", "clean_text": "On June 5, 2013, the board held a regularly scheduled meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, the board reviewed with Mr. Sadove and Saks\u0092 advisors the discussions with each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Company B\u0092s principal shareholders regarding potential transactions, and authorized (1) the implementation of a process to determine whether a transaction with one of the potential acquirors which had executed a confidentiality agreement could be reached on terms that would offer attractive value to Saks shareholders and (2) the submission of a revised proposal to acquire Company B.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June 5, 2013", "normalized": "2013-06-05", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B026", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 26, "start_line": 1202, "end_line": 1203, "raw_text": "On June 6, 2013, Saks submitted a revised and non-binding proposal with a higher price to acquire Company\nB in a cash transaction, with flexibility to include some stock consideration.", "clean_text": "On June 6, 2013, Saks submitted a revised and non-binding proposal with a higher price to acquire Company B in a cash transaction, with flexibility to include some stock consideration.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June 6, 2013", "normalized": "2013-06-06", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B027", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 27, "start_line": 1205, "end_line": 1207, "raw_text": "During the week of June 10, 2013, Saks was informed\nthat a privately held retail company, which we refer to as Company F, had indicated interest in participating with Sponsor A and Sponsor E in a potential acquisition of Saks. Company F engaged in due diligence of Saks. However, no meetings were held\nbetween representatives of Saks and representatives of Company F, and Company F did not participate in the offer that was ultimately submitted by Sponsor A and Sponsor G.", "clean_text": "During the week of June 10, 2013, Saks was informed that a privately held retail company, which we refer to as Company F, had indicated interest in participating with Sponsor A and Sponsor E in a potential acquisition of Saks. Company F engaged in due diligence of Saks. However, no meetings were held between representatives of Saks and representatives of Company F, and Company F did not participate in the offer that was ultimately submitted by Sponsor A and Sponsor G.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June 10, 2013", "normalized": "2013-06-10", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B028", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 28, "start_line": 1209, "end_line": 1210, "raw_text": "During the second and third weeks of June, representatives of Saks, including members of management, held multiple meetings with representatives of Sponsor A and Sponsor E as part of Sponsor A\u0092s and\nSponsor E\u0092s due diligence evaluation of Saks.", "clean_text": "During the second and third weeks of June, representatives of Saks, including members of management, held multiple meetings with representatives of Sponsor A and Sponsor E as part of Sponsor A\u0092s and Sponsor E\u0092s due diligence evaluation of Saks.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June", "normalized": null, "precision": "unknown"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B029", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 29, "start_line": 1212, "end_line": 1213, "raw_text": "On July 2, 2013, at the direction of Saks, Goldman Sachs distributed a draft merger\nagreement and process details to each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Sponsor E, with a request for submission of offers for an all-cash acquisition of Saks, along with comments on the draft merger agreement, no later than July 11, 2013.", "clean_text": "On July 2, 2013, at the direction of Saks, Goldman Sachs distributed a draft merger agreement and process details to each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Sponsor E, with a request for submission of offers for an all-cash acquisition of Saks, along with comments on the draft merger agreement, no later than July 11, 2013.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 2, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-02", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "July 11, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-11", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B030", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 30, "start_line": 1215, "end_line": 1216, "raw_text": "On July 5, 2013, Saks received a letter from Company B\u0092s principal shareholders indicating that Saks\u0092 proposed price in its\npreviously submitted proposal was still insufficient for the principal shareholders of Company B to consider entering into a transaction, and stating the minimum proposed purchase price that would be required in", "clean_text": "On July 5, 2013, Saks received a letter from Company B\u0092s principal shareholders indicating that Saks\u0092 proposed price in its previously submitted proposal was still insufficient for the principal shareholders of Company B to consider entering into a transaction, and stating the minimum proposed purchase price that would be required in", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 5, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-05", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B031", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 31, "start_line": 1218, "end_line": 1218, "raw_text": "-25-", "clean_text": "-25-", "is_heading": true, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "other"}
{"block_id": "B032", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 32, "start_line": 1221, "end_line": 1223, "raw_text": "order for Company B\u0092s principal shareholders to consider a potential acquisition of Company B by Saks. Company B\u0092s principal shareholders, however, suggested that Saks\u0092 senior\nmanagement meet with their counterparts at Company B, to discuss, among other items, potential synergies, which might assist in closing the valuation gap. After consultation between board members and members of Saks\u0092 senior management, it was\ndetermined that Saks\u0092 senior management would not meet with Company B\u0092s management in light of the substantial differences in the parties\u0092 position, including on price, and the other transactions being considered.", "clean_text": "order for Company B\u0092s principal shareholders to consider a potential acquisition of Company B by Saks. Company B\u0092s principal shareholders, however, suggested that Saks\u0092 senior management meet with their counterparts at Company B, to discuss, among other items, potential synergies, which might assist in closing the valuation gap. After consultation between board members and members of Saks\u0092 senior management, it was determined that Saks\u0092 senior management would not meet with Company B\u0092s management in light of the substantial differences in the parties\u0092 position, including on price, and the other transactions being considered.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B033", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 33, "start_line": 1225, "end_line": 1227, "raw_text": "In early July 2013, Sponsor E informed Saks that Sponsor A was no longer intending to be a primary participant in a potential transaction and that\nSponsor E had entered into discussions with Sponsor G, a private equity firm, regarding a potential joint acquisition of Saks. On July 8, 2013, Saks entered into a confidentiality agreement with Sponsor G. Following execution of the\nconfidentiality agreement, representatives of Saks, including members of management, met with representatives of Sponsor E and Sponsor G as part of their due diligence evaluation of Saks.", "clean_text": "In early July 2013, Sponsor E informed Saks that Sponsor A was no longer intending to be a primary participant in a potential transaction and that Sponsor E had entered into discussions with Sponsor G, a private equity firm, regarding a potential joint acquisition of Saks. On July 8, 2013, Saks entered into a confidentiality agreement with Sponsor G. Following execution of the confidentiality agreement, representatives of Saks, including members of management, met with representatives of Sponsor E and Sponsor G as part of their due diligence evaluation of Saks.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "early July 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-05", "precision": "month_early"}, {"raw_text": "July 8, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-08", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B034", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 34, "start_line": 1229, "end_line": 1230, "raw_text": "On July 10, 2013, the Finance committee of the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, Goldman Sachs updated the\ncommittee members regarding the process to solicit offers from Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor E and Sponsor G and the ongoing discussions with Company B\u0092s principal shareholders.", "clean_text": "On July 10, 2013, the Finance committee of the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, Goldman Sachs updated the committee members regarding the process to solicit offers from Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor E and Sponsor G and the ongoing discussions with Company B\u0092s principal shareholders.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 10, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-10", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B035", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 35, "start_line": 1232, "end_line": 1237, "raw_text": "On July 11, 2013, each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, on the one hand, and Sponsor E, together with Sponsor G, on the other hand, submitted proposals expressing their continued interest in an acquisition of\nSaks. Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s proposal included a price of $15.25 per share of common stock, a revised draft merger agreement and information and documentation relating to Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s committed debt and equity financing for the\npotential transaction. The joint proposal from Sponsor E and Sponsor G included an indicative price range of $14.50\u0096$15.50 per share of common stock, but noted that the parties would require several weeks to continue their due diligence\nevaluation in order to submit a more definitive proposal and did not include a revised draft merger agreement or any documents supporting availability of financing for the proposal. Saks was subsequently informed that Sponsor G was no longer\nparticipating in the process, and that Sponsor E would again be joined in its proposal by Sponsor A as a primary participant. Saks\u0092 negotiations with Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Sponsor E did not include any discussions regarding\npost-closing employment terms for the Company\u0092s executives or senior management.", "clean_text": "On July 11, 2013, each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, on the one hand, and Sponsor E, together with Sponsor G, on the other hand, submitted proposals expressing their continued interest in an acquisition of Saks. Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s proposal included a price of $15.25 per share of common stock, a revised draft merger agreement and information and documentation relating to Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s committed debt and equity financing for the potential transaction. The joint proposal from Sponsor E and Sponsor G included an indicative price range of $14.50\u0096$15.50 per share of common stock, but noted that the parties would require several weeks to continue their due diligence evaluation in order to submit a more definitive proposal and did not include a revised draft merger agreement or any documents supporting availability of financing for the proposal. Saks was subsequently informed that Sponsor G was no longer participating in the process, and that Sponsor E would again be joined in its proposal by Sponsor A as a primary participant. Saks\u0092 negotiations with Hudson\u0092s Bay, Sponsor A and Sponsor E did not include any discussions regarding post-closing employment terms for the Company\u0092s executives or senior management.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 11, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-11", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B036", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 36, "start_line": 1239, "end_line": 1241, "raw_text": "Upon the further suggestion of the principal\nshareholders of Company B that direct discussions between the senior management of the parties would be productive, on July 13, 2013, senior management of Saks met with senior management of Company B to discuss the possibility of an acquisition\nof Company B and the potential role of management of Company B following the proposed acquisition of Company B by Saks.", "clean_text": "Upon the further suggestion of the principal shareholders of Company B that direct discussions between the senior management of the parties would be productive, on July 13, 2013, senior management of Saks met with senior management of Company B to discuss the possibility of an acquisition of Company B and the potential role of management of Company B following the proposed acquisition of Company B by Saks.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 13, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-13", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B037", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 37, "start_line": 1243, "end_line": 1243, "raw_text": "During the week of", "clean_text": "During the week of", "is_heading": true, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B038", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 38, "start_line": 1244, "end_line": 1245, "raw_text": "July 15, 2013, at the direction of the board, representatives of Goldman Sachs indicated to representatives of Sponsor A and Sponsor E that a proposed purchase price in the lower half of the previously submitted price range would not be\nacceptable to the board in light of the $15.25 bid from Hudson\u0092s Bay and the board\u0092s view of the Company\u0092s value.", "clean_text": "July 15, 2013, at the direction of the board, representatives of Goldman Sachs indicated to representatives of Sponsor A and Sponsor E that a proposed purchase price in the lower half of the previously submitted price range would not be acceptable to the board in light of the $15.25 bid from Hudson\u0092s Bay and the board\u0092s view of the Company\u0092s value.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 15, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-15", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B039", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 39, "start_line": 1247, "end_line": 1247, "raw_text": "On", "clean_text": "On", "is_heading": true, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B040", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 40, "start_line": 1248, "end_line": 1251, "raw_text": "July 17, 2013, the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, the board reviewed the proposal from Hudson\u0092s Bay and the joint proposal from Sponsor E and\nSponsor A and the status of discussions with Company B\u0092s principal shareholders. The board discussed these potential transactions for Saks as compared to the merits and considerations of remaining as a standalone entity. The board authorized\nGoldman Sachs to inform each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, on the one hand, and Sponsor E and Sponsor A, on the other hand, that their initial price proposals were insufficient and authorized Wachtell Lipton to provide a revised draft of the merger\nagreement to Hudson\u0092s Bay and its counsel.", "clean_text": "July 17, 2013, the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs and Wachtell Lipton. At this meeting, the board reviewed the proposal from Hudson\u0092s Bay and the joint proposal from Sponsor E and Sponsor A and the status of discussions with Company B\u0092s principal shareholders. The board discussed these potential transactions for Saks as compared to the merits and considerations of remaining as a standalone entity. The board authorized Goldman Sachs to inform each of Hudson\u0092s Bay, on the one hand, and Sponsor E and Sponsor A, on the other hand, that their initial price proposals were insufficient and authorized Wachtell Lipton to provide a revised draft of the merger agreement to Hudson\u0092s Bay and its counsel.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 17, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-17", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B041", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 41, "start_line": 1253, "end_line": 1254, "raw_text": "On July 18, 2013, Wachtell Lipton provided a revised draft of the merger agreement to\nrepresentatives of Hudson\u0092s Bay.", "clean_text": "On July 18, 2013, Wachtell Lipton provided a revised draft of the merger agreement to representatives of Hudson\u0092s Bay.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 18, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-18", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B042", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 42, "start_line": 1256, "end_line": 1257, "raw_text": "Also on July 18, 2013, Saks entered into a confidentiality agreement with Company B for Saks to\nengage in due diligence with respect to Company B. Thereafter, during the second and third weeks of July, members of", "clean_text": "Also on July 18, 2013, Saks entered into a confidentiality agreement with Company B for Saks to engage in due diligence with respect to Company B. Thereafter, during the second and third weeks of July, members of", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 18, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-18", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "July", "normalized": null, "precision": "unknown"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
