{"block_id": "B057", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 57, "start_line": 1312, "end_line": 1313, "raw_text": "On July 26, 2013, Mr. Sadove and Mr. Baker met to\ndiscuss Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s potential acquisition of Saks. At this meeting Messrs. Sadove and Baker discussed certain remaining open issues regarding the transaction, and Mr. Sadove discussed the results of the quarter to date.", "clean_text": "On July 26, 2013, Mr. Sadove and Mr. Baker met to discuss Hudson\u0092s Bay\u0092s potential acquisition of Saks. At this meeting Messrs. Sadove and Baker discussed certain remaining open issues regarding the transaction, and Mr. Sadove discussed the results of the quarter to date.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 26, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-26", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B058", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 58, "start_line": 1315, "end_line": 1317, "raw_text": "Also on July 26, 2013, the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC\n(a long-time advisor to Saks, referred to as \u0093 Morgan Stanley\u0094) and Wachtell Lipton. The board, Saks\u0092 management and the legal and financial advisors again reviewed the terms of the proposal by Hudson\u0092s Bay, and discussed the\nstatus of negotiations with Hudson\u0092s Bay.", "clean_text": "Also on July 26, 2013, the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC (a long-time advisor to Saks, referred to as \u0093 Morgan Stanley\u0094) and Wachtell Lipton. The board, Saks\u0092 management and the legal and financial advisors again reviewed the terms of the proposal by Hudson\u0092s Bay, and discussed the status of negotiations with Hudson\u0092s Bay.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 26, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-26", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B059", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 59, "start_line": 1319, "end_line": 1323, "raw_text": "On July 28, 2013, the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives\nof Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley and Wachtell Lipton. The board, Saks\u0092 management and the legal and financial advisors again reviewed the terms of the proposal by Hudson\u0092s Bay, including as compared to the merits and considerations of\nremaining as a standalone entity. Representatives of Goldman Sachs reviewed with the board Goldman Sachs\u0092s financial analysis of the $16 per share of common stock in cash to be paid to Saks\u0092 shareholders in the proposed merger and then\ndelivered to the board Goldman Sachs\u0092s oral opinion, subsequently confirmed in writing, that, as of such date and based upon and subject to the various limitations and assumptions set forth in the opinion, the $16 per share of common stock in\ncash to be paid to the holders of common stock pursuant to the merger agreement was fair, from a financial point of view, to such holders. See \u0093 The Merger (Proposal 1)\u0097 Opinion of Goldman, Sachs & Co.", "clean_text": "On July 28, 2013, the board held a special telephonic meeting attended by representatives of Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley and Wachtell Lipton. The board, Saks\u0092 management and the legal and financial advisors again reviewed the terms of the proposal by Hudson\u0092s Bay, including as compared to the merits and considerations of remaining as a standalone entity. Representatives of Goldman Sachs reviewed with the board Goldman Sachs\u0092s financial analysis of the $16 per share of common stock in cash to be paid to Saks\u0092 shareholders in the proposed merger and then delivered to the board Goldman Sachs\u0092s oral opinion, subsequently confirmed in writing, that, as of such date and based upon and subject to the various limitations and assumptions set forth in the opinion, the $16 per share of common stock in cash to be paid to the holders of common stock pursuant to the merger agreement was fair, from a financial point of view, to such holders. See \u0093 The Merger (Proposal 1)\u0097 Opinion of Goldman, Sachs & Co.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 28, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-28", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B060", "document_id": "0001193125-13-390275", "ordinal": 60, "start_line": 1325, "end_line": 1326, "raw_text": "Following the board\u0092s approval of the merger and the merger agreement, Saks, Hudson\u0092s Bay and Merger Sub\nfinalized and executed the merger agreement and other transaction documents later on July 28, 2013.", "clean_text": "Following the board\u0092s approval of the merger and the merger agreement, Saks, Hudson\u0092s Bay and Merger Sub finalized and executed the merger agreement and other transaction documents later on July 28, 2013.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "July 28, 2013", "normalized": "2013-07-28", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
